In science, we often invoke the phrase that we "stand on the shoulders of giants": that science is rarely a solitary act but rather a series of collaborative endeavors building upon the work of those that have come before. This work is no exception. I believe, however, that as much as this applies to the science, it also applies to the scientist. I am very much the product of incredible colleagues, friends, and family that have built me up over this journey. 

I am probably doing a poor job of writing an acknowledgements section proper. However, if I detailed everyone I believe is worth acknowledging and the roles they have played in this journey, this section would go on for pages upon pages. So in lieu of penning all your names in this work, I hope to instead look forward and promise to express my gratitude in years to come through conversations and laughter and shared experiences and, most importantly, a shoulder to lean on as we continue to build each other up - for ourselves and for those who come after. 




